content.p:
The Governing System consists of Governing Bodies and Governing Executive Systems.
Execution Framework Proposals (EFPs) are Proposals which make decisions and operate procedures;
Executive Policy Charters (EPCs) are Charters which settle Policies, Rules and Regulations;
Executive Research Dossiers (ERDs) are Dossiers which Governing Researches shall be made.

A Proposal or a Charter may directly inherit another one from another Governing System,
when both Systems share the same mandatory features and functionalities;
in an inheritance, alignments of Things to this System shall be declared in the same Proposal.

Within this Board, a Supreme Governing Group shall be formed jointly by an Executive Leadership
and a Chief Governance Officer;
amendments and interpretations of this Constitution must be approved by Supreme Governing Group.

Execution Framework Proposals (EFPs) are formal procedures to Executions in this Constitution;
they may provide standards, methods, and structured execution plans,
including but not limited to strategies, projects, guidelines and advice.

A Proposal to initiations or amendments to a Charter shall be proposed via this Process;
a submission of the corresponding Charter must be enclosed jointly for Process of Charters;
the body of Proposal of Charter must only contain non-normative information to the Charter
while the main, normative body of the Charter remains in the main file of it.

Executive Policy Charters (EPCs) are formal authoritative forms of
Policies, Rules and Regulations in this Constitution;
they shall be led by Governing Bodies;
they may also establish organizational principles, governance structures, and policies.
